Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"NPropagate", "::", "usage"}], "=", 
   "\"\<NPropagate[EventsAndTimings, opts][\[Rho]ini] propagates an initial \
density operator \[Rho]ini under a consecutive sequence of events, returning \
the final density operator. If \[Rho]ini is a vector representation, the \
output is also a vector representation. If \[Rho]ini is a symbolic operator, \
the output is also a symbolic operator. If opts contains \
Continuous\[Rule]True, the output is a OperatorTrajectoryFunction which may \
be evaluated at any time point within the timing range of the propagation. \
The options InitialTimePoint\[Rule]tini or FinalTimePoint\[Rule]tfin may be \
given to specify the time origin of the event sequence. \n\n\tThe item \
EventsAndTimings is a list of events. The possible formats for each event \
are:\n(i) a single superoperator, assumed to act instantaneously;\n(ii) have \
the form {Hop,\[Tau]} where Hop is a time-independent Hamiltonian operator, \
acting over the interval \[Tau];\n(iii) have the form {Lsop,\[Tau]}, where \
Lsop is a time-independent Liouvillian superoperator, acting over the \
interval \[Tau];\n(iv) the form {Function[t,f[t]],\[Tau]} where f[t] is an \
operator or superoperator expression dependent on the time variable t. The \
time-dependent operator or superoperator acts over the interval \[Tau];\n(v) \
the form {PeriodicFunction[t,T,f[t]],\[Tau]} where f[t] is a periodic \
operator or superoperator expression with period T.  The periodic \
time-dependent operator or superoperator acts over the interval \[Tau];\n(vi) \
the form {TimeDependentGeneratorFunction[..],\[Tau]} where the \
TimeDependentGeneratorFunction object allows specification of a \
time-dependent Hamiltonian or Liouvillian dependent on either a global or \
local time variable, or both. \n\n\tThe call to NPropagate may include \
options for the NDSolve routine, used in cases (iv) and (v). The operator \
basis used in the calculation may be specified if desired using the \
OperatorBasis option.\n\t\n\tThe option BackgroundGenerator\[Rule]background \
may be used in NPropagate. The term background may be an operator, a \
superoperator, an operator function, and so on (the format is the same as any \
of the individual events). When this option is used, the term background is \
combined with all of the items in the sequence of events. \n\n\tThe two \
options UseMatrixExpWhenPossible, UseHilbertSpaceWhenPossible and \
UseDiagonalizationWhenPossible may be used to control the propagation \
strategy. These options take the values True or False.\n\n\tThe output of \
NPropagate is an operator, for the case Continuous\[Rule]False, or an \
OperatorTrajectoryFunction, for the case Continuous\[Rule]True.\n\>\""}], 
  ";"}]], "Input",
 PageWidth:>WindowWidth,
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.452685645562502*^9, 3.45268596259144*^9}, {
   3.452686007045341*^9, 3.452686024085301*^9}, {3.45268620091995*^9, 
